case_circumstances: The subject was found by Homeland Security agents that were patrolling a desert area near Gila Bend Arizona. He is believed to be an immigrant who was traveling on foot to the United States. He was in the possession of multiple Mexican identification cards bearing the name Eduardo Morales Ponce as well as documentation from a Mexican prison regarding an arrest on 3/17/2013  in Mexico.

case_clothing_with_body: Also found with the body was a camoflage "EXMA" shirt a black hat and one grey sock.

case_other_items_with_body: Also found with the body was a black wallet, too cigarette lighters, Chapstick, two Mexican identification cards with the name is Eduardo Antonio Morales Ponce, a religious card, two pennies, two pesos, and empty water bottle, one pink pill, an empty "Idoex" bottle, and documentation that indicated the subject had been arrested in Mexico for robbery with violence which was listed as first offense.
